CONSTRAINT RULES

each constraint has to be split by underscore and begins with a modifier (letter)


-name, -na
exact string match; case-insensitive

-slots, -sl
string find match
default: "012"

-refine, -re
string find match, comma separated list of numbers, or prefixed with <, <=, >, >=
default behavior (exclude the option): all
examples:
-re 3,4
-re >=10,4

-stock, -st
-buyers, -bu
-price, -pr

-enchant, -en
exact string match; case-insensitive
enum: sharp, sharp blade, arch, zeal, 

-enchantlevel, -el
string find match
default: "1234"

-category, -ca
enum: weapon, armor, garment, offhand, footgear, accessory, headwear, blueprint, card, item, scroll, album

-subcategory, -sc
enum: bow, staff, spear, mace, sword, knife, head, tail, face, mouth, back

b - broken
d - not broken

